---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How much does cane toad removal usually cost?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Typical South Florida pricing is about $120-$190 for an initial visit and about $100-$170 per month for recurring maintenance."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is recurring service worth it?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "For many homes, yes. Reinfestation pressure from nearby properties often makes recurring visits more effective than repeated one-time calls."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What factors increase pricing?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Larger properties, high toad density, complex landscaping, and emergency scheduling can all increase total cost."
      }
    }
  ]
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Cane Toad Removal Cost in Florida: Typical Pricing by Service Type"
  description="Cane toad removal cost guide for South Florida homeowners. Compare one-time, emergency, and recurring service pricing and learn what affects total monthly cost."
  schema={schema}
>
  <div class="urgency">
    <strong>⚠️ Pet safety first:</strong> If exposure already happened, go to
    <a href="/cane-toad-dog-poisoning/"> the emergency guide</a>.
  </div>

  <div class="hero">
    <h1>Cane Toad Removal Cost in South Florida</h1>
    <p>Most homeowners pay for an initial cleanup plus recurring visits. Exact pricing depends on property size, density of toads, and whether emergency response is needed.</p>
    <a href="/cane-toad-removal/" class="btn btn-lg">Get a Local Quote →</a>
  </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h2>Typical Price Ranges</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Initial visit:</strong> about $120-$190</li>
      <li><strong>Recurring monthly service:</strong> about $100-$170/month</li>
      <li><strong>Emergency/same-night visit:</strong> can be significantly higher</li>
      <li><strong>Larger properties:</strong> usually priced per visit by acreage</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What Drives the Cost</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Lot size and landscaping complexity</li>
      <li>Standing water features and irrigation patterns</li>
      <li>Frequency of visits needed during peak season</li>
      <li>Whether egg-string removal and prevention planning are included</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>One-Time vs Recurring Service</h2>
    <p>A single visit can quickly reduce numbers, but neighboring populations often repopulate yards. Recurring service is usually more cost-efficient than repeated emergency calls over time.</p>

    <h2>How to Get Better Value</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Ask for a written scope of services.</li>
      <li>Confirm if nighttime collection is included.</li>
      <li>Check whether egg removal is part of the plan.</li>
      <li>Pair professional visits with habitat fixes at home.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Already seeing toads? <a href="/cane-toad-removal/">Connect with a removal pro →</a></p>

    <h2>Related Pages</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/cane-toad-florida/">Cane Toad Florida guide</a></li>
      <li><a href="/how-to-get-rid-of-cane-toads/">DIY control options</a></li>
      <li><a href="/toad-proof-fencing/">Toad-proof fencing</a></li>
    </ul>

    <h2>FAQ</h2>
    <div class="faq">
      <details>
        <summary>How much does cane toad removal usually cost?</summary>
        <p>Most homeowners see initial pricing around $120-$190 and monthly maintenance around $100-$170 depending on property conditions.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Is recurring service worth it?</summary>
        <p>Usually yes, especially in neighborhoods with steady reinfestation pressure from surrounding properties.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What factors increase pricing?</summary>
        <p>Large lots, dense landscaping, severe activity, and emergency scheduling can all raise cost.</p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
